      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RENTESSIS (1) missed the kick then went through his gears well to get up for fourth last start over 1030m at Grafton. Perfectly placed out to this distance at the third run back from a spell. Lightly raced three-year-old who looks ready to double the win tally. THE LUPERCAL (3) doesn't win out of turn but his recent efforts have been sound in shorter races than this. Up a little in grade today but gets some welcomed weight relief. One of the better chances. RETHINK IT (6) failed by a head over this course and distance in heavy going two back then disappointed over 1400m at Inverell last time. Can bounce back off a five-week freshen up. MONTE OUTLANDER (4) probably needs this run but he is always competitive at this circuit.",
